.TH "snd_pcm_notify" 9 "snd_pcm_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_notify \- Add/remove the notify list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_notify
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_notify *notify "  ","
.BI "int nfree "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "notify" 12
PCM notify list
.IP "nfree" 12
0 = register, 1 = unregister
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This adds the given notifier to the global list so that the callback is
called for each registered PCM devices.  This exists only for PCM OSS
emulation, so far.
